## Models Already Defined

### User Model (`src/models/user.model.js`) — COMPLETE, DO NOT MODIFY
- Fields: name, email, password (bcrypt, select:false), phone, role (user/admin/superAdmin/vendor), isBlocked, address (addressSchema), wishlist (ref: Product), resetPasswordToken, resetPasswordExpire
- Methods: comparePassword(), getResetPasswordToken()
- Pre-save hook: bcrypt password hashing (salt 12)
- Address schema fields: fullName, phone, houseNo, area, landmark, city, state, pincode, country

### All Other Models — EMPTY, need to be written

---

## Coding Conventions — STRICTLY FOLLOW

### General
- CommonJS only: `require()` and `module.exports` — NO ES modules (no import/export)
- All async route handlers must be wrapped in `asyncHandler` utility
- Always use `ApiResponse` for success responses and `ApiError` for error responses
- No `console.log` in production code — use proper error handling
- All controllers must have try-catch via asyncHandler

### Naming
- Files: `feature.type.js` → e.g., `auth.controller.js`, `user.routes.js`
- Variables/functions: camelCase
- Models/Classes: PascalCase
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Routes: kebab-case → `/api/v1/auth`, `/api/v1/user`, `/api/v1/admin`

### Response Format — ALWAYS use this structure
```js
// Success
res.status(200).json(new ApiResponse(200, data, "Success message"))

// Error
throw new ApiError(400, "Error message")
```

### JWT Strategy
- User: Access Token (15m) + Refresh Token (7d) — stored in httpOnly cookies
- Admin: Separate Access Token (15m) + Refresh Token (7d) — stored in httpOnly cookies
- Secrets from env: JWT_ACCESS_SECRET, JWT_REFRESH_SECRET, JWT_ADMIN_ACCESS_SECRET, JWT_ADMIN_REFRESH_SECRET

### Utils to build first (before anything else)
1. `src/utils/ApiResponse.js` — Standard success response class
2. `src/utils/ApiError.js` — Custom error class extending Error
3. `src/utils/asyncHandler.js` — Async wrapper for controllers
4. `src/utils/tokenUtils.js` — generateAccessToken, generateRefreshToken, generateAdminAccessToken, generateAdminRefreshToken

